# Trivy Ignore Configuration for Serverless Blog Infrastructure
# Requirements: 12.2, 12.5
#
# This file defines exceptions for Trivy security scanning.
# Keep synchronized with .checkov.yaml skip rules.
#
# Format: AVD-AWS-XXXX or avd-aws-XXXX
# See: https://avd.aquasec.com/ for rule details
#
# Phase 2: Local Defense (Trivy pre-commit)
# - Block HIGH/CRITICAL severity issues locally
# - Allow documented exceptions for business/architecture reasons

# ======================================
# S3 Bucket Rules
# ======================================

# AVD-AWS-0089: S3 bucket has logging disabled
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_18 - CloudTrail provides audit trail.
# Terraform state bucket cannot log to itself.
AVD-AWS-0089

# AVD-AWS-0090: S3 bucket does not have versioning enabled
# Note: NOT ignored - versioning IS enabled on all buckets

# AVD-AWS-0132: S3 bucket does not have cross-region replication configured
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_145 - single-region application.
# S3 versioning provides sufficient disaster recovery.
AVD-AWS-0132

# ======================================
# DynamoDB Rules
# ======================================

# AVD-AWS-0024: DynamoDB table point-in-time recovery not enabled
# Note: NOT ignored - PITR IS enabled on DynamoDB table

# AVD-AWS-0025: DynamoDB table uses AWS managed encryption
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_119 - AWS-managed keys sufficient
# for non-PII blog post data.
AVD-AWS-0025

# ======================================
# Lambda Rules
# ======================================

# AVD-AWS-0066: Lambda function does not have a DLQ
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_116 - synchronous Lambda functions
# return errors to API Gateway clients directly.
AVD-AWS-0066

# AVD-AWS-0067: Lambda function environment variables not encrypted
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_173 - no secrets in env vars.
# Sensitive values use Secrets Manager.
AVD-AWS-0067

# AVD-AWS-0121: Lambda does not have tracing enabled
# Note: Conditionally ignored - X-Ray enabled in prd environment only.
# This may trigger in dev environment configurations.
AVD-AWS-0121

# ======================================
# API Gateway Rules
# ======================================

# AVD-AWS-0001: API Gateway access logging not enabled
# Note: This should NOT be ignored for production.
# TODO: Enable access logging in modules/api

# AVD-AWS-0004: API Gateway domain not using TLS 1.2
# Note: NOT ignored - TLS 1.2 minimum is configured

# AVD-AWS-0190: API Gateway endpoint is publicly accessible
# Justification: Same as CKV2_AWS_29 - required for CloudFront.
# Cognito authorizers protect sensitive endpoints.
AVD-AWS-0190

# ======================================
# CloudFront Rules
# ======================================

# AVD-AWS-0011: CloudFront distribution does not have WAF enabled
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_86 - WAF adds cost.
# Rate limiting at CloudFront level; no PII data.
AVD-AWS-0011

# AVD-AWS-0012: CloudFront distribution logging disabled
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_68 - S3 storage cost.
# CloudWatch metrics provide sufficient visibility.
AVD-AWS-0012

# AVD-AWS-0013: CloudFront does not use custom TLS certificate
# Note: NOT ignored - CloudFront viewer certificate configured

# AVD-AWS-0010: CloudFront uses outdated TLS version
# Note: NOT ignored - TLSv1.2_2021 security policy configured

# ======================================
# Cognito Rules
# ======================================

# AVD-AWS-0022: Cognito User Pool does not have MFA configured
# Note: Conditionally ignored - MFA is set to OPTIONAL, not OFF.
# This may trigger false positive for OPTIONAL setting.
AVD-AWS-0022

# ======================================
# CloudWatch Rules
# ======================================

# AVD-AWS-0017: CloudWatch log group not encrypted with CMK
# Justification: Same as CKV_AWS_158 - no PII in logs.
# Default encryption is sufficient.
AVD-AWS-0017

# ======================================
# General/Terraform Rules
# ======================================

# Note: Trivy does not check module source versioning like Checkov.
# CKV_TF_1/CKV_TF_2 equivalents are not applicable in Trivy.

# ======================================
# Synchronization Note
# ======================================
# This file should be kept in sync with .checkov.yaml
# When adding/removing skip rules:
# 1. Update both .checkov.yaml and .trivyignore
# 2. Document justification in both files
# 3. Run: pre-commit run --all-files (to verify Trivy)
# 4. Run: checkov -d . (to verify Checkov)
